# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Create a matrix that are Transpose of the initial matrix and compare each row of initial matrix to each row of its transpose matrix when its equal just increment ans.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
- O(n*n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
- O(n^2)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int equalPairs(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        int ans=0,cnt=0;
        int n=grid.size();
        vector<vector<int>>v(n,vector<int>(n,0));

     for(int i=0;i<grid.size();i++){

        for(int j=0;j<grid.size();j++){
         // transpose matrix
         v[j][i]=grid[i][j];
        } 

     }
    for(int i=0;i<grid.size();i++){
      for(int j=0;j<grid.size();j++) {
//      compare row of transpose matrix and initial matrix
          if(v[j]==grid[i]){
              ans++;
          }
      }

    }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

