I used 3 Maps
1. Cuisine to food so we can get all food of that cuisine. I used a TreeSet to keep everything ordered. TreeSet is a binary search tree (Red Black Tree to be precise) so it's balanced. 
2. Food to Cuisine so we can know where to find the food TreeSet when updating the rating
3. Food to Rating (can be avoided if we created a custom class).

Lessons
1. TreeSet uses the comparator to see if your element exists in the TreeSet (might not be correct, that's from personal experiments). Thus, remove the element, THEN update the rating, THEN insert again. Don't do update, remove, insert. This way, TreeSet will contain duplicates.
2. Always use .equals() to compare Objects. That includes Integer. ```foodToRat.get(a)==(foodToRat.get(b))``` actually would break the code! HashMap.get() returns an Integer. 
```
