## Bellow points would cast time in contest but you can able to avoid wa submission and it's best practice for interview purpose. 
Well, for such question where design is more important than the logic, we have to write bug free code. Because once you get the error in code than it's hard to debug while in the contest because of large number of code.
*  So hint to write clean solution :
	*  Always write a variable name which have clear explanation, will help to quick debug.
	*  Try to enacpsulat as much as possible in single entity, It will help to handle the data.
	*  Split the design in class/function and each function must have only one task to do, So this will help to give confidence that if this function is correct you don't need to check again
	*  Always check **Null Pointer exception** and that's the major problem when you tackel with language like java.
	*  For debug/print perpuse override toString function of your class, due to this you can simply put sout and see the data.
	*  Always write code in well farmated manner, leetcode doesn't give feature to auto-formate, So make habit of it.
	*  Avoid redundant code, it'll give your code in smaller line, so smaller code will take smaller time to debug and you skip the typing time cast.


```
class Data {
    String food;
    String cuisine;
    int rating;
    public Data(String food, String cuisine, int rating) {
        this.food = food;
        this.cuisine = cuisine;
        this.rating = rating;
    }
    public void set(String food, String cuisine, int rating) {
        this.food = food;
        this.cuisine = cuisine;
        this.rating = rating;
    }
    public String toString() {
        return food+" "+" "+cuisine+" "+rating;
    }
}

class FoodRatings {
    Map<String, Data> nameToData;
    Map<String, TreeSet<Data>> csToData;

    private void add(String food, String cuisine, int rating) {
        String combine = rating+food;
        Data data = nameToData.getOrDefault(food, null);

        if(data!=null && csToData.containsKey(data.cuisine)) {
            TreeSet<Data> set = csToData.get(data.cuisine);
            if(set!=null) {
                set.remove(data);
                if(set.size()==0) {
                    csToData.remove(data.cuisine);
                }
            }
        }

        if(data == null) {
            data = new Data(food, cuisine, rating);
        }
        data.set(food, cuisine, rating);
        nameToData.put(food, data);
        if(!csToData.containsKey(cuisine)) {
            csToData.put(cuisine, new TreeSet<>((a,b)->{
                if(a.rating == b.rating) {
                    return -1*(a.food.compareTo(b.food));
                }
                return a.rating-b.rating;
            }));
        }
        csToData.get(cuisine).add(data);
    }

    public FoodRatings(String[] foods, String[] cuisines, int[] ratings) {
        nameToData = new HashMap<>();
        csToData = new HashMap<>();
        for(int i=0;i<foods.length;i++) {
            add(foods[i], cuisines[i], ratings[i]);
        }
    }

    public void changeRating(String food, int newRating) {
        add(food, nameToData.get(food).cuisine, newRating);
    }

    public String highestRated(String cuisine) {
        return csToData.get(cuisine).last().food;
    }
}
```

