solutions.content:
**Intuition :**

* Idea here is to keep track of food and cuisine using food. This would help in updating ratings and get top rated food of particular.

* To get highest rated food of given cuisine, we need a `cuisineMap` that would store `rating` and `food`. 
	* **`{cuisine, set{rating, food}}`**
	* Each cuisine has a set that contains multiple foods and their ratings, sorted by ratings
	* This will be useful in getting top rated food.
* To update rating of given food, we need a `foodMap` that would store `rating` and `cuisine`. 
	* **`{food, {rating, cuisine}}`**
	* We will use this cuisine value to update cuisine map as well with `newRating`

*Note :* 
* Store rating as `negative` value so we get highest rated food at the top of set in `cuisineMap`.
* SO in case of tie i.e same rating, we will get lexicographically smallest `food` string.
# Code :

```
class FoodRatings {
    unordered_map<string, set<pair<int, string>>> cuisineMap; // { cuisine, set{ rating, food } }
    unordered_map<string, pair<int, string>> foodMap; // { food, { rating, cuisine } }

public:

    FoodRatings(vector<string>& foods, vector<string>& cuisines, vector<int>& ratings) {
        int n = foods.size();

        // Create cuisines and foods mapping
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++) {
            cuisineMap[cuisines[i]].insert({-ratings[i], foods[i]}); // Cuisine -> {Rating, Food}
            foodMap[foods[i]] = {-ratings[i], cuisines[i]}; // Food -> {Rating, Food}
        }
    }

    void changeRating(string food, int newRating) {
        auto [currentRating, cuisine] = foodMap[food]; // Get existing rating to find this food in cuisine

        foodMap[food] = {-newRating, cuisine}; // Update with new rating

        // Now update rating and food for particular cuisine
        cuisineMap[cuisine].erase({currentRating, food}); // Remove old value
        cuisineMap[cuisine].insert({-newRating, food}); // Insert new value
    }

    string highestRated(string cuisine) {
        // First element in set of cuisine will be highest rated (-ve of rating is lowest)
        return cuisineMap[cuisine].begin()->second;
    }
};
```

