# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Thinking in faster retrival perspective, Constructor initalized one time can take more time to load. Post construct, methods should return result faster.

Used multiple `hashtable` to know `cuisine` against `food`, `rating` aginst `food` and `food-rating` collection against `cuisine` (Collections thought for faster response of `highestRated` method.).

PriorityQueue for storing food rating in sorted manner
`new PriorityQueue<FoodRating>((p1, p2) -> (p1.rating==p2.rating) ? p1.food.compareTo(p2.food) : p2.rating-p1.rating)`

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$Constructor = O(n*log(n) 
- changeRating = O(log(n)) 
- highestRated = O(1)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
