solutions.content:
Let’s say 
**n(A)** denotes the number of set bits in **‘A’**.
**n(B)** denotes the number of set bits in **‘B’**.

Then **n( A & B )** denotes the number of set bits in **‘A&B’**.
And **n( A | B)** denotes the number of set bits in **‘A|B’**.

If we convert this problem to set theory, 
Then it will look like this.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/34825a73-a4f2-461b-b267-700c9864ccda_1658635426.6096902.jpeg)



**n(A)** 	    will be “Blue+Yellow”
**n(B)** 	    will be “Yellow+Green”
**n( A&B )**  will be “Yellow”
**n( A|B )**    will be “Blue+Yellow+Green”

Now, what we want is,
**n( A&B ) + n( A|B ) >=k**

**“Yellow” + “Blue+Yellow+Green” >=k**

It is same as,
**“Blue + Yellow” + “Yellow + Green”>=k**

**n(A) + n(B) >=k**.

So, our ultimate target is to calculate number of distinct pairs (a,b) where 
(number of set bits of a + number of set bits of b) >=k.

**Step 1:** Maintain one set of given numbers to avoid duplicates.
**Step 2:** Maintain the frequency array. Where freq[i] denotes the number of elements having i number of set bits.
**Step 3:** Now we want to calculate the pairs (a,b) such that, n(a) + n(b) >=k
**Step 4:** For this, iterate over every element of the set(mentioned in Step 1). Let’s say the current number is ‘curr’, and it is having a ‘cnt’ number of set bits. A pair (curr,x) is valid, if n(x)>=k-cnt. Now we want to find the number of elements having set bits count greater than (k-cnt). Evaluate it using, freq array.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int cntSetBits(int n){
        int ans=0;
        // cout<<n<<' ';
        while(n){
            if(n&1){
                ans++;
            }
            n=(n>>1);
        }
        // cout<<ans<<'\n';
        return ans;
    }
    long long countExcellentPairs(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        long long ans=0;
        vector<long long>freq(63);
        set<int>st(nums.begin(),nums.end());
        for(auto n:st){
            freq[cntSetBits(n)]++;
        }
        for(auto n:st){
            int my=cntSetBits(n);
            int least=max(0,k-my);
            for(int i=least;i<63;i++){
                ans+=freq[i];
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

