solutions.content:
First of all, remove the duplicates from the array, since we only want unique answers. We can use map or set to get unique elements. There is a property that the sum of the number of set bits in ```num1 | num2``` and ```num1 & num2``` is equal to the set bits in the sum of the two number.
For example: if num1 = 4, num2 = 8 then the set bits in ```num1 | num2``` is 2 and set bits in ```num1 & num2``` is 0. The sum of the number num1 and num2, ```12``` also contains 2 + 0 set bits.
We can use this property to solve the question optimally.

 Now, we make another array which contains set bits of the numbers. 
 If the given array was ```[1,2,3,1,536870911]```, then we can make another array ```[1,1,2,29]```. Now we will operate on this array only. We first sort the array. Then we can use binary search to find the lower bound of (k - nums[i]) to find the number of possible answer for that index. Below is the code.

 ```
 class Solution {
public:
	// Function to find number of set bits in a number
    int setBits(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n) {
            count += n & 1;
            n >>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
    long long countExcellentPairs(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        unordered_map<int,int> mp;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++) {
            mp[nums[i]] = 1;
        }
        vector<int> realNums; // new array which contains set bits
        for(auto &it: mp) {
            realNums.push_back(setBits(it.first)); // store set bits
        }
        sort(realNums.begin(), realNums.end()); // sort the array to perform binary search
        long long ans = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<realNums.size();i++) {
            int curr = realNums[i];
			   int target = k - curr;
            int j = lower_bound(realNums.begin() + i, realNums.end(), target) - realNums.begin(); // find target in the right part of the array, we will not consider left part.
            long long total = realNums.size() - j; // total numbers lying on right part satisfying the condition
           // If the same number also satisfy the condition then we dont want to consider it twice
			   if(j == i) { 
					ans++;
					if(total-1) {
						ans += 2 * (total-1);
					}
				} 
            else {
                ans += 2*total; // (num1,num2) and (num2,num1) both possibility
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
 ```

