# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)
- Space complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
  public long countExcellentPairs(int[] nums, int k) {
    Map<Integer, Set<Integer>> bitCountMap = new HashMap<>();
    long countEP = 0;

    for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
      int acc = nums[i];
      int cntSet = 0;
      while (acc != 0) {
        cntSet += ((acc & 1) == 1 ? 1 : 0);
        acc = acc >> 1;
      }

      if (bitCountMap.containsKey(cntSet) && bitCountMap.get(cntSet).contains(nums[i])) {
        continue;
      }

      if (bitCountMap.containsKey(cntSet)) {
        bitCountMap.get(cntSet).add(nums[i]);
      } else {
        Set<Integer> b = new HashSet<>();
        b.add(nums[i]);
        bitCountMap.put(cntSet, b);
      }

      if (2 * cntSet >= k) {
        countEP += 2 * bitCountMap.get(cntSet).size() - 1;
      }
    }

    for (int j = 1; j <= 32; j++) {
      if (bitCountMap.containsKey(j) && k - j < j) {
        long s = 0;
        int t = Math.max(k - j, 1);
        while (t < j) {
          if (bitCountMap.containsKey(t)) {
            s += bitCountMap.get(t).size();
          }
          t++;
        }

        countEP += 2 * bitCountMap.get(j).size() * s;
      }
    }

    return countEP;
  }
}
```

