# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Or + And of two numbers is same as bit count of Both numbers 

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We will find set bits of all the numbers. And then go through the sorted array and find the sum >= k. We can also use Binary search to find the res. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n), iteration is once(O(n) set, O(n) in bit vector)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n), storing in set 

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int findSetBit(int x){
        int cnt = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<32; i++){
            if(x & (1 << i)) cnt++; //if bit is set
        }
        return cnt;
    }
    long long countExcellentPairs(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        set<int> st; //to store unique elements
        for(auto i: nums) st.insert(i);

        vector<int> bit;

        for(auto i: st){
            int setBit = findSetBit(i);
            bit.push_back(setBit); //pusing set bits count of each number
        }
        sort(bit.begin(), bit.end());

        int n = bit.size();   
        int l= 0; 
        int r = n-1; 
        long long res = 0;
        while(l < n && r >= 0){ //as two way res works 1,2  n  2,1
            int sum = bit[l] + bit[r]; //sum of bit cnt of two numsj = num1 OR num2 + num1 AND num2 

            if(sum < k){
                l++; //increase value and explore
            }
            else{ //if >= k
                res += (n - l); //+ values in the subarray
                r--;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

