# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. find all distinct elements (use set)
2. push the set bit cnt to new vector 
3. sort new vector containing the bits cnt
4. traverse the vector and find lowerbound idx for (k-v[i]) all elements after the lowerbound considering the itself are a valid pair 
5. increse the cnt
6. return cnt

Note : for getting setbit cnt inbuild C++ STL __builtin_popcount();

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O{n(log n)}

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(n)
