solutions.content:
**Method:**

* The important fact is to realize that
* **```number of set bits in OR(X,Y) + number of set bits in AND(X,Y) = number of set bits in X + number of set bits in Y```**
* so now we will store the number of set bits of each element in vector "v" and then count the pair(i,j) such that ```v[i]+v[j]>=k```
* Now, we can further optimize it
	* we don't have to store the duplicates
	* if ```v[i]==v[j]``` then the number of pairs will be 1
	* else the number of pairs = 2 ({i,j},{j,i})
	* so to remove the duplicates we can use set
* To further optimize it we can sort the vector array v
* why?
	* so now we have an array in increasing order of number of set bits
	* Now, we can do binary search to find the required pair
		* ```l=0, r=v.size()-1```
		* note that
			* ``` if (v[l] + v[r] >= k)```
			* then sum of all the pairs between l and r will be >=k
			* because ```v[l+1]>=v[l]```
			* so we can just simply add all those pair to the ans
			* i.e ```ans+= (r-l)```
			* now as we said above when the elements are distinct then there will be two pair for each i and j so we need to multiply the ans by 2 here
			* i.e ```ans+= (r-l)*2```
* we can take care of the same element pair (i,i) while pushing the set bits in v by checking 
	``` 
	if (2 * cnt >= k)
          ans++;
	```

**Code:**

```
class Solution
{
public:
    unsigned int calc(unsigned int n)
    {
        unsigned int count = 0;
        while (n)
        {
            count += n & 1;
            n >>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
    long long countExcellentPairs(vector<int> &nums, int k)
    {

        set<int> st(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        long long ans = 0;
        vector<int> v;
        for (auto x : st)
        {
            int cnt = calc(x);
            if (2 * cnt >= k)
                ans++;
            v.push_back(cnt);
        }
        sort(v.begin(), v.end());
        int l = 0;
        int r = v.size() - 1;
        while (l < r)
        {
            if (v[l] + v[r] >= k)
            {
                ans += (r - l) * 2;
                r--;
            }
            else
                l++;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

