solutions.content:
X AND Y + X OR Y == X bit count + Y bit count.

We calculate counts for all bossible bit numbers (from 1 to 31, from 1 to 10^9).
When just checking all possible bits combinations some of them will have a non-zero count. 

```
public class Solution {
    public long CountExcellentPairs(int[] nums, int k) {
        int[] bits = new int[31];

        foreach(int num in nums.Distinct()){
            int count = CountBits(num);
            bits[count]++;
        }

        long ans = 0;

        for(int i=1; i<31; i++){
            for(int j=1; j<31; j++){
                if(i+j >= k){
                    ans += bits[i]*bits[j];
                }
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }

    private int CountBits(int num){
        int count =0;
        while(num >0){
            count += num&1;
            num >>=1;
        }

        return count;
    }
}
```

